{"add":{"doc":{"id":"48cd918fb2690e6e07f8023d9aa5719893058da30276b9a4371724248da88b1c","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Erneststatue.jpg/220px-Erneststatue.jpg","previous":[],"after":["In 1851, the King undertook a number of journeys around Germany. He accepted an invitation from the Prussian Queen-consort to visit Charlottenburg Palace, near Berlin.[109] He visited Mecklenburg for the christening of the Grand Duke's son, and Lüneburg to inspect his old regiment. In June Ernest celebrated his 80th birthday by playing host to the King of Prussia. Late that summer, he visited Göttingen, where he opened a new hospital and was given a torchlight procession.[110]"]}}}